quasars.name: Quasar #2852
quasars.description: A short descriptor of the asset.

assets.title: Anxious Pleasures - Amy Elkins
assets.description: For 377 consecutive days, from the day the lockdown started until Elkins received her COVID vaccine, she took one self portrait. The collection shows her whimsy, boredom, frustration and courage - and reflects what many around the world have felt over the past year.

assets.title: The Rizzo Collection - Alberto Rizzo
assets.description: The Rizzo Collection by Alberto Rizzo is a 100 piece collection selected by the Rizzo family in concert with BeetsDAO to represent the best of his body of work. 2.5% of the primary sale will be donated to St. Jude's Hospital.

assets.title: Privileged Mediocrity - Kris Graves
assets.description: Privileged Mediocrity by Kris Graves examines systemic unfairness in the United States. Represented by Sasha Wolf Projects.

assets.title: Ethiopia - Joey L
assets.description: Joey L's Ethiopia is a monolithic collection made over the course of thirteen years. It is an ode to every region of the country and a celebration of all the unique peoples found within.

assets.title: Homegrown - Julie Blackmon
assets.description: Blackmon carefully sets her scenes, but like film and theater directors, she is in pursuit of unscripted moments that provoke, disturb, and challenge the viewer.

assets.title: Touching Strangers - Richard Renaldi
assets.description: Touching Strangers embodies the human desire to connect despite our differences.

assets.title: Bushes and Succulents - Mona Kuhn
assets.description: Bushes & Succulents is Mona Kuhn's celebration of the female essence - confident, raw and elegant, yet confrontational and unapologetic.

assets.title: Rumors of Arctic Belonging - Kiliii Yuyan
assets.description: The Arctic is changing radically. In his impressive series, Kiliii Yuyan offers insight into the fascinating imagery of the North.

assets.title: Miscommunicated Secrets - Mercedes Jelinek
assets.description: Miscommunicated Secrets began with obsessive tendencies—the need to make new things based on un-photographable feelings.

assets.title: New Yorkers - Sally Davies
assets.description: Davies started the New Yorkers by shifting from her usual view of the urban outdoors to the idea of chronicling the spaces and stories of the natives and transplants who give the city its particular vitality.

assets.title: Divine - Delphine Diallo
assets.description: Delphine Diallo's intention is for every woman she photographs to feel the image she makes of them is a personal gift. “I am not taking pictures, I am giving pictures,” as Diallo puts it.

assets.title: ICONS - Parker Day
assets.description: Parker Day's ICONS invites us to approach identity with a sense of play and malleability, and to recognize the forgotten parts of ourselves as we see them reflected in these color-saturated portraits.
